{"title":"How to watch the Tour de France Femmes 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-tour-de-france-femmes","date":1723109573000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-tour-de-france-femmes\">How to watch the Tour de France Femmes 2024</a></p>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\" target=\"_blank\">Tour de France Femmes</a> is upon us. The third edition of the race will start with a Dutch Grand Départ on Monday 12th August 2024.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>During the eight stages of the 2024 Tour de France Femmes, the race will travel southwards from the Netherlands <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-de-france-femmes-climbs\" target=\"_blank\">down to the Alps </a>with a finale set on Sunday 18th August atop <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/alpe-d-huez-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">Alpe d’Huez</a>. The race will take in a <em>parcours </em>of 947.9km in total, including one individual time-trial around Rotterdam on Stage 3.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes-favourites\" target=\"_blank\">The favourites</a> coming into the 2024 edition are Demi Vollering of SD Worx-ProTime, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elisa-longo-borghini-cyclist\" target=\"_blank\">Elisa Longo Borghini</a> of Lidl-Trek and Juliette Labous of DSM-Firmenich-PostNL. Other stars competing this August include Kasia Niewiadoma, Lizzie Deignan, Lorena Wiebes and Puck Pieterse.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>How to watch and live stream the Tour de France Femmes</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-970x647.png\" alt=\"tour de france femmes\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402-350x233.png 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T181418.402.png 1800w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Charly Lopez</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tour de France Femmes will be broadcast throughout the UK and Europe on Eurosport 1. The channel will also host their panel pre and post-race show ‘The Breakaway’ throughout the race. Luckily, timings also mean that all races will be shown live on Eurosport 1. There are no clashes caused by the Vuelta, which starts later this month.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also stream the racing and ‘The Breakaway’ on <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fget.discoveryplus.com%2Fgb%2Fwatch-entertainment-and-sport%3Futm_medium%3Dsearch%26utm_source%3Dpmax%26gad_source%3D1%26gclid%3DCj0KCQjw8MG1BhCoARIsAHxSiQlg0iGYIjmoKvq-9hgG6l1y1G0hfLEkG4B3H3E1q8Q2eTe5LG1uZ5UaAr1XEALw_wcB\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> for £6.99 per month with the basic package, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. The service allows uninterrupted coverage without advert breaks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Ireland, free-to-air coverage will be broadcast live with <a href=\"https://www.tg4.ie/en/irish-tv-schedule/sport-schedule/\" target=\"_blank\">Irish-language commentary on TG4</a>. S4C will show the racing with Welsh-language coverage.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It is being broadcast across 198 countries, but it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find a way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month, with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes-predictions-2024\">Cyclist’s Tour de France Femmes predictions 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-de-france-femmes-climbs\">The climbs that will decide the Tour de France Femmes 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes-favourites\">Who are the favourites for the Tour de France Femmes 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\">Tour de France Femmes 2024: Route, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Tour de France Femmes official broadcasters</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-970x647.png\" alt=\"demi vollering tour de france femmes\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134-350x233.png 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T180748.134.png 1800w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Thomas Maheux</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Abu Dhabi:</strong> Abu Dhabi Sports<br /><strong>Asia (excluding China and Japan): </strong>Eurosport Asia-Pacific<br /><strong>Australia:</strong> SBS<br /><strong>Belgium:</strong> RTBF, VRT<br /><strong>Canada:</strong> FloBikes<br /><strong>Central and South America:</strong> ESPN<br /><strong>Denmark:</strong> DKTV2<br /><strong>Europe:</strong> Eurosport<br /><strong>France:</strong> France TV Sport, France 24<br /><strong>Germany:</strong> One 1, Sportschau<br /><strong>Ireland:</strong> TG4<br /><strong>Japan:</strong> JSports<br /><strong>Netherlands:</strong> NOS<br /><strong>New Zealand:</strong> Sky Sport<br /><strong>Norway:</strong> TV2<br /><strong>Spain:</strong> Caracol, RCN, RTVE<br /><strong>Subsaharan Africa:</strong> Supersport<br /><strong>Switzerland:</strong> SRG-SSR<br /><strong>United States:</strong> CNBC, Peacock</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de France Femmes 2024 broadcast times</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-970x647.png\" alt=\"tour de france femmes\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326-350x233.png 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/08/file-2024-08-07T182242.326.png 1800w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Charly Lopez</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All times BST and subject to change by broadcasters</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Monday 12th August</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>11:00-15:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 11:00-15:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Tuesday 13th August</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>08:30-11:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 08:30-11:15<strong> </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Tuesday 13th August</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:30-17:15<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 14:30-17:15<strong> </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Wednesday 14th August</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>12:30-15:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 12:30-15:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Thursday 15th August</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>12:30-15:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 12:30-15:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: Friday 16th August</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>12:30-15:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 12:30-15:30</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 7: Saturday 17th August</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>12:00-15:15<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 12:00-15:15</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 8: Sunday 18th August</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>15:00-18:30<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 15:00-17:30</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Want to know more about the Tour de France Femmes 2024? Read <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\">our full guide </a>including stage profiles and startlist.</em></p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes-predictions-2024\">Cyclist’s Tour de France Femmes predictions 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-de-france-femmes-climbs\">The climbs that will decide the Tour de France Femmes 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes-favourites\">Who are the favourites for the Tour de France Femmes 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-femmes\">Tour de France Femmes 2024: Route, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                      